        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We propose observations of Orion BN/KL using a single setup in band 7 (0.9 mm) in many molecular species. 

Correlator setup. 
We will use four spectral windows with bandwidth of 938 MHz and channel spacing of 0.49 MHz, corresponding to a velocity resolution of 0.42 km/s.
Our correlator setup will cover the CH3CN (19-18), C34S (7-6), CH3OH (7-6),
C17O (3-2), SiO (8-7), H13CO+ (3-2), H2CO, HNCO(16-15), and SO (10-10) lines. 
These includes molecules that have been shown to trace in (high-mass) star forming regions rotating structures (CH3CN, C34S, CH3OH, C17O),
infall motions (H2CO, CS, C17O), 
and jets/outflows (SiO, H13CO+, SO).

Imaging/Pointings. 
We request three Pointings to cover the entire Hot Core region as well as BN.
We require the highest angular resolutions of 0.12 arcsec to achieve the three science goals described in Sect. 1.2: 
1) to resolve emission from close compact continuum sources, for ex. Source I from the Hot Core or from SMA1 (1" apart); 
2) to study the chemistry in the interface between the Source I outflow and the hot core peak (within 1"); 
3) to resolve the outflow from Source I perpendicular to its axis as well as (possibly) its accretion disk (&gt;0.2").  
Since the most extended configuration filters out low-brightness, extended emission on scales &gt;7.2 arcsec in both the hot core and the outflow from Source I (extended over 12"), we also require the ACA 7-m Array.

Sensitivity and time requested. 
Based on previous SMA observations at 0.9mm (Beuther et al. 2005) and ALMA observations at 1.3mm (Niederhofer et al. 2012), the proposed molecular lines have flux density peaks &gt;2 Jy at 1arcsec (see also Table 1 in the scientific justification). To ensure ALMA can detect transitions with flux density peaks &gt;30 mJy with a 0.12 arcsec beam with SNR&gt;3, we need to reach an rms noise of 10 mJy in a channel of 0.42 km/s. According to the ALMA time estimator, this requires 1.1 h for the 12m-array and 3 h for ACA, over 3 fields (including
calibration).</prj:justificationText>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
